                <h2>Database conventions</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Naming conventions</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Tables:</strong> Plural nouns in Pascal case (e.g., Risks, Actions)</li>
                    <li><strong>Columns:</strong> Pascal case (e.g., Title, DueDate)</li>
                    <li><strong>Primary keys:</strong> Always named <code>Id</code></li>
                    <li><strong>Foreign keys:</strong> Entity name + "Id" (e.g., ObjectiveId, OwnerUserId)</li>
                    <li><strong>Junction tables:</strong> Combination of both entity names (e.g., RiskActions)</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Data type conventions</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>INTEGER:</strong> Used for IDs, numeric ratings, percentages</li>
                    <li><strong>VARCHAR:</strong> Used for titles, names, emails with specified max lengths</li>
                    <li><strong>TEXT:</strong> Used for descriptions, notes, and long-form content</li>
                    <li><strong>DATETIME:</strong> Always stored in UTC</li>
                    <li><strong>BOOLEAN:</strong> Used for flags (IsDeleted, IsActive, etc.)</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Constraints and validation</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>All primary keys are auto-incremented</li>
                    <li>Required fields are marked as NOT NULL</li>
                    <li>Foreign keys include ON DELETE CASCADE or RESTRICT as appropriate</li>
                    <li>Rating fields have CHECK constraints for valid ranges (1-5)</li>
                    <li>Email fields have format validation</li>
                    <li>Status fields use CHECK constraints for valid values</li>
                </ul>

